title: For Sale/Trade:  AR 15
postcontent:
Tired of these outrageous prices? Here is a cheap alternative that will give you a better rifle. 
Assemble your own AR 15 for $600-$1000 depending on your options.
Go to gunbroker.com, buy a stripped lower receiver for anywhere between $100-250. It may take a while to find a good one, but you can get a forged aluminum receiver for under $200 or a polymer for $150 with the complete lower.
Then go search sites like Rguns for the upper and lower or other parts sites. There are over a dozen sites out there with inventory in stock for parts. You can get complete uppers or get it in parts, same goes for lowers. 
This is a great way to customize your rifle and really get to know it. Not to mention you can at least get the upper assembled while you wait for the receiver to go through background checks.

Some of these rifles out there are going for $1,500-$3,000 and you could build a better rifle easily with $1,000. A build is easy, you can follow youtube videos for instructions. You also get to pick stuff like polymer vs aluminum receiver, 1/7 vs 1/9 barrel twist, wide variety of sights, stocks, handrail options out the wazoo, all black vs a bi-tone. 

Dont pay these outrageous prices. If you want a good reference as to what rifles should cost, look below. If you see a stock rifle going for more than the below price, I suggest you pass and build your own!
Palmetto State Armory $999
M&P15 Sport $799
Stag Arms Model 3 $999
Windham Weaponry $1039
DPMS A3 $899
DPMS AP4 $999
Bushmaster Carbon $899
Delton M4 $899

(I am not selling anything, just promoting you build instead of paying jacked prices to these gougers. If you want sites, go to google and search, I am not an expert, just a gun lover on a budget)
